<br>
I am keeping up with the WoW information as regards PvP, and I'm just going to have to wait to either play it, or hear about the PvP from beta testers.  I'm undecided about the instanced PvP I've read about.  I'm not sure how that would work, honestly.<br>
<br>
However, I must give Blizzard the benefit of the doubt in this area.  They are not stupid, they are also gamers, and I'll bet my left foot they have played all the current games on the market between them, and know what the good and bad things are about those games and the PvP systems.  Their number one criteria is that the game be fun, and I have the feeling that, whatever they come up with, it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be fun, even if it's not exactly what we've come to expect from DAoC.<br>
<br>
To be sure, I'm not sure I want a PvP system exactly like Camelot's.  Right now it's the best system out there if you can ignore RAs, MLs, character balance, artifacts, etc.  That doesn't mean, however, it's the only system.  <br>
<br>
My biggest fear with WoW is that it will be pointless PvP.  While I enjoy the act of fighting other players, it adds so much more to my gaming experience to have a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>reason</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to do so.  I really like the realm vs. realm aspect, of having a reason to go out there and kill the invaders, and to have a common ground to share with the other realm players.  I don't just want to beat someone else up, I want to kill the scurvy invaders, protect my family, and defend my realm.  That, to me, is so much more fun than just logging into a zone to find other players to fight for no reason.  If that's all it is, we might as well just have dueling arenas, and in all my years of playing EQ, I went to an arena exactly twice.<br>
<br>
Now, I could definitely get into an Alliance vs. Horde conflict.  If there is an AvH server, I would of course try to get all the Lears over there to participate in the defense of the Alliance.   But that remains to be seen, so all we can really do, like everyone else, is wait.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><font size=2>Moomba MacLear<br>
